{{Expand Dutch|Arteveldetoren|date=April 2018}}

The '''Artevelde Tower''' (official Dutch name: '''KBC Arteveldetoren''') is an office building in the [[Belgium|Belgian]] city of [[Ghent]]. The tower is 118,5 metres and the highest building of Ghent and the highest office in the [[Flemish Region]]. It hosts the regional headquarters of a bank-insurer [[KBC Bank|KBC]]. The [[groundbreaking]] was held in March 2010, and the highest point was reached at the beginning of July 2011. The building was officially inaugurated on April 20, 2012.{{cn|date=April 2018}}

== External links ==
