"'''Bank Alert'''" is a 2016 song by Nigerian [[pop music|pop]] duo [[P-Square]]. It was recorded in [[Igbo language|Igbo]] and Pidgin English and samples lyrics from "Iyogo" by [[Onyeka Onwenu]].<ref name="P-Square6">{{cite news|author=Jasper Efe|title=P-Square – Bank Alert|url=http://dailypost.ng/music/2016/09/16/p-square-bank-alert/|accessdate=18 September 2016|work=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post]]|date=16 September 2016}}</ref> It was released as a [[free download]] on 15 September and the next day, the accompanying [[music video]] was released on [[YouTube]].<ref name="P-Square1">{{cite news|author=|title=P-Square Return With New Single ‘Bank Alert’|url=http://www.okayafrica.com/in-brief/p-square-new-single-bank-alert-mp3-download/|accessdate=18 September 2016|work=Okay Africa|date=16 September 2016}}</ref> The video was directed by [[Clarence Peters]] and Jude Okoye with cameo appearances by [[Phyno]], [[Harrysong]], [[Kcee (musician)|Kcee]], Onyeka Onwenu and Mr. Ibu among others.<ref name="P-Square">{{cite news|author=|title=P-Square return with colourful new video for ‘Bank Alert’|url=http://www.thenet.ng/2016/09/p-square-return-with-colourful-new-video-for-bank-alert/|accessdate=18 September 2016|work=Nigerian Entertainment Today|date=17 September 2016}}</ref>
As of 22 September 2016, "Bank Alert" has received over one million views.<ref name="Bank Alert">{{cite news|author=|title=1 million views in 5 days for P-Square’s ‘Bank Alert’ show they are still a force|url=http://thenet.ng/2016/09/1-million-views-in-5-days-for-p-squares-bank-alert-show-they-are-still-a-force/|accessdate=23 September 2016|work=Nigeria Entertainment Today|via=|date=22 September 2016}}</ref>
A reviewer from ''Okay Africa'' described it as a "catchy song built on light guitars, bubbly synthesizers and a shuffling beat."<ref name="P-Square1"/>
