{{Distinguish|Interstate Aviation Committee}}

The '''Federal Air Transport Agency''' ({{lang-ru|Федеральное агентство воздушного транспорта}}), also known as '''Rosaviatsiya''' ({{lang-ru|Росавиация}}), is the [[Government of Russia|Russian government]] agency responsible for overseeing the [[civil aviation]] industry in Russia. Its headquarters are in [[Moscow]].<ref>[http://www.favt.ru Home page]. Federal Air Transport Agency. Retrieved on January 3, 2012. "Адрес 125993, ГСП-47, Москва, Ленинградский проспект, 37, корпус 2."</ref>

It is also called the Russian Federation Civil Aviation Administration (RFCAA).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aibn.no/ra-85621-pdf?pid=Native-ContentFile-File&attach=1 |title=Report on the Accident to Vnukovo Airline's Tupolev Tu-154M RA 85621 Near Svalbard Airport Longyear, Norway on 29 August 1996 |author=[[Accident Investigation Board Norway]] |date=2 November 1999 |accessdate=21 August 2014}} p. 5/121.</ref>

The Federal Air Transport Agency regularly works alongside the [[Interstate Aviation Committee]] in investigations of [[aviation accidents and incidents]]. Its U.S. equivalent is the [[Federal Aviation Administration]].

