{{Infobox mountain | name = La Luette | photo = Dix.jpg | photo_caption = [[Mont Blanc de Cheilon]] center and La Luette (center right) seen from Lac des Dix | elevation_m = 3548 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 179 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is the Col de la Luette (3,369 m).</ref> | parent_peak = [[Le Pleureur]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Valais]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Pennine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|0|37.2|N|7|23|15.4|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''La Luette''' is a [[mountain]] of the [[Pennine Alps]], located between the valleys of [[Bagnes]] and [[Val d'Hérens|Hérens]] in the canton of [[Valais]]. It lies just south of [[Le Pleureur]].
