The '''National Library of Benin''' ({{lang-fr|Bibliothèque nationale du Bénin}}) is the [[legal deposit]] [[library]] for [[Benin]]. It was created on 27 November 1975 and is located in the [[Ouando]] neighbourhood of [[Porto-Novo]]. According to the United Nations, as of 2012 approximately 32 percent of adult Beninese [[Literacy#Literacy in Africa|can read]].<ref name=UnescoLiteracy>{{cite web|url= http://data.uis.unesco.org/Index.aspx?DataSetCode=EDULIT_DS&popupcustomise=true&lang=en# |title= Adult literacy rate, population 15+ years (both sexes, female, male) |publisher= [[UNESCO Institute for Statistics]] |location=Montreal |work=UIS.Stat |accessdate=19 August 2017 }}</ref>

For many years the directory of the National Library was [[Florence Ayivi Foliaon]].<ref name="HoungnikpoDecalo2012">{{cite book|author1=Mathurin C. Houngnikpo|author2=Samuel Decalo|title=Historical Dictionary of Benin|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3G3XyLV6b4cC&pg=PA19|date=14 December 2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7373-5|pages=19–}}</ref>

