'''Priessnitz''' is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[rock band]] from [[Jeseník]] formed in 1989. The band has released 9 albums, the last one named "''Beztíže''" (Zero Gravity) was released in October 2016 <sup>[1]</sup>. In 2016 [http://www.ceskatelevize.cz/porady/11012868471-kombo/416234100051010-priessnitz-v-tancirne-v-racim-udoli the Czech Television made a medallion of the band], in which the viewer is introduced to the almost 30-year history of Priessnitz. In 2016, the band was nominated for the [[:cs:Ceny Apollo#2016|music prize Apollo]] for the album ''Beztíže'' by the Czech music critics. The Academy of Popular Music in the Czech Republic nominated Priessnitz in the categories of song of the year (Mrzáci) and group of the year as part of the music awards ''[[:cs:Ceny Anděl 2016|Ceny Anděl 2016]]''. ==Discography== ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/freiwaldau Freiwaldau]'', Legend/1992, Indies Records/2002 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/nebel Nebel]'', Legend/1992, Indies Records/2003 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/hexe Hexe]'', Bonton, 1994 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/seance Seance]'', Indies Records, 1996 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/potichu Potichu?]'', Indies Records, 1997 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/zlaty-dest Zlatý déšť]'' (singl), Indies Records, 1999 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/zero Zero]'', EMI/Escape, 2001 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/playlist Playlist]'', EMI/Escape, 2004 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/strepy Střepy]'' (singl), EMI/Escape, 2006 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/stereo Stereo]'', EMI/Escape, 2006 ** ''[http://priessnitz.com/beztize Beztíže]'', Supraphon, 2016
