{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Shunqing |local = 天主教顺庆教区 |latin = Dioecesis Scioenchimensis |country = [[China]] |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Chongqing|Chongqing]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Chongqing|Chongqing]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = Cathedral of the Sacred Heart of Jesus in [[Nanchong]] |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 25,000 |population = 8,000,000 |population_as_of = 1950 |catholics = 19,442 |catholics_percent= 0.2 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = |metro_archbishop = [[Sede Vacante]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Shunqing/Shunking/Nanchong''' ({{lang-la|Scioenchimen(sis)}}, {{zh|順慶, 南充}}) is a [[suffragan]] Latin [[diocese]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Chongqing|Chongqing]] in southwest China, yet depends on the missionary [[Roman Congregation for the Evangelization of Peoples]].
Its [[cathedral]] episcopal see is the Cathedral of the [[Sacred Heart of Jesus]], in the Shunqing city center district of [[Nanchong]] 南充, [[Sichuan]] province. No statistics available.
== History == * Established on 2 August 1929 as '''[[Apostolic Vicariate]] of [[Shunqingfu]]''' 順慶府 / Shunkingfu / de Shunkingfu (Latin) [[Fu (country subdivision)|-fu]] meaning administrative prefecture], on territory split off from the then [[Apostolic Vicariate of Chengdu]] 成都 (now a diocese) * Promoted on April 11, 1946 and renamed after its see as '''Diocese of Shunqing''' 順慶 / Nanchong 南充 (中文) / Shunking / Sciœnchimen(sis) (Latin).
==Episcopal ordinaries== (all [[Roman Rite]] native Chinese)
;''Apostolic Vicar of Shunqingfu 順慶府 * Paul Wang Wen-cheng (王文成) (December 2, 1929 – April 11, 1946 ''see below'')
;''Suffragan Bishops of Shunqing 順慶 * [[Paul Wang Wen-cheng]] (王文成) (''see above'' April 11, 1946 – January 28, 1961) *''uncanonical: Fan Dao-jiang (范導江) (1963 – death 1987.12.17), without papal mandate *''uncanonical: Michael Huang Wo-ze (黃渥澤) (1989 – retired 2001), without papal mandate; died 2004 * Joseph Chen Gong-ao (陳功鰲) (2012 – ...)
