{{Infobox Union |name= Industrifacket |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] |members= 90,000 |full_name= Swedish Industrial Union |native_name= Industrifacket |image= |founded= 1993 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= January, 2006 |dissolved_state= Merged into |merged_into= [[IF Metall]] |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= [[Leif Ohlsson]], president |website= [http://www.industrifacket.se www.industrifacket.se] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Swedish Industrial Union''' (Industrifacket) was a general [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It was formed in 1993 by the merger of the Factory Worker's Union and the Textile, Garment and Leather Workers' Union.
In January, 2006 the Swedish Industrial Union merged with the [[Swedish Metalworkers' Union]] to form [[IF Metall]].
